<h1>Installing software</h1>

<p>Download latest <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspbian/">Raspbian</a> and follow <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/installation/installing-images/README.md">install instructions</a>.
<a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/remote-access/ssh/">Ssh into</a> Raspberry Pi and run:
<code>
sudo raspi-config
</code>
Expand file system, enable camera and then reboot.
Run this to install git:
<code>
sudo apt-get install git
</code>
Git clone tarina and then run install script with sudo:
<code>
git clone https://rbckman@bitbucket.org/rbckman/tarina.git
cd tarina
sudo ./install.sh
</code>
You'r ready to rumble:
<code>
python tarina.py
</code></p>

